  <h2 class="no-num no-toc">Abstract</h2>

  <p>When authors adapt their sites for high-resolution displays, they
  often need to be able to use different assets representing the same
  image. We address this need for adaptive, bitmapped content images by
  adding a <code>srcset</code> attribute to the <code>img</code>
  element.</p>

  <h2 class="no-num no-toc">Status of This document</h2>

<!--BOILERPLATE middle-feedback-->
<!--BOILERPLATE middle-w3c-html-module-status-->

  <p>Work on this specification was formerly done at the <a href="http://www.whatwg.org/">WHATWG</a>
  in its HTML Living Standard. As of <a
  href="http://html5.org/tools/web-apps-tracker?from=8611&to=8612">r8612</a>, the Living Standard
  pulls in an external document for the definition of the <code>img</code> element. This
  specification is based on the relevant sections of the Living Standard prior to that change.</p>

  <div>
    <p>The following features are <strong>at risk</strong> and may be
    removed due to lack of implementation.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>the <i>width descriptor</i> and  <i>width descriptor value</i>.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

